# 4-In-A-Row
It is a simple board game, made with openGL. 
Our Computer graphics project is a game that all of us has played a lot in our childhood. 
Itâ€™s called 4-in-a-row. 
It is a board game of 2 players, where each player is given a color (in our game red or yellow) which they have to match, 4 colored coins horizontally, vertically or diagonally.
